  C0["<b>Current repo</b><br/>- present now: AGENTS.md, docs/<br/>- not detected: .codex/, .agents/skills/, AGENTS.override.md<br/>- map shows supported optional structure"] 
  C1["<b>Global AGENTS</b><br/>- personal reusable guidance<br/>- loaded before repo guidance<br/>- override wins when present"] 
  C2["<b>Global config.toml</b><br/>- user config shared by CLI + IDE<br/>- model, provider, approvals, sandbox<br/>- MCP, hooks, feature flags, log_dir"] 
  C3["<b>Custom agents</b><br/>- optional user-scoped spawned-agent defs<br/>- inherit normal config keys<br/>- useful for specialized workflows"] 
  C4["<b>log/</b><br/>- default is $CODEX_HOME/log<br/>- docs mention codex-tui.log<br/>- session-*.jsonl only if enabled"] 
  C5["<b>prompts/</b><br/>- verify in official docs<br/>- not verified in current docs snapshot<br/>- not treated as a supported layer here"] 
  C6["<b>User skills</b><br/>- official global skill location is $HOME/.agents/skills<br/>- not under ~/.codex<br/>- SKILL.md is required entrypoint"] 
  C7["<b>Skill extras</b><br/>- scripts: executable helpers<br/>- references: docs loaded on demand<br/>- assets: templates/resources<br/>- agents/openai.yaml: UI metadata, invocation policy, tool deps"] 

  C8["<b>Repo AGENTS</b><br/>- persistent repo instructions<br/>- build/test/lint rules<br/>- conventions and do-not rules"] 
  C9["<b>Nested override</b><br/>- per directory, Codex checks override first<br/>- only one instruction file per directory<br/>- closer directories win later in merge"] 
  C10["<b>Project config.toml</b><br/>- trusted projects only<br/>- layers stack from repo root to cwd<br/>- overrides user config for matching keys"] 
  C11["<b>Hooks config</b><br/>- discovered via hooks.json or inline [hooks]<br/>- matching hooks from multiple layers all run<br/>- user/system hooks still load in untrusted repos"] 
  C12["<b>Hook scripts</b><br/>- script folder is a convention, not discovery<br/>- official examples use .codex/hooks/<br/>- scripts must be referenced explicitly"] 
  C13["<b>Project custom agents</b><br/>- optional repo-scoped spawned-agent defs<br/>- good for team-specific specialist agents"] 
  C14["<b>Repo skills</b><br/>- official path is .agents/skills<br/>- Codex scans cwd up to repo root<br/>- replaces requested top-level skills/ sketch"] 
  C15["<b>docs/</b><br/>- normal project docs<br/>- not a special Codex discovery path<br/>- good place for generated onboarding docs"] 

  C16["<b>Built-in slash commands</b><br/>- session controls, not repo files<br/>- /init, /model, /permissions, /mcp<br/>- /agent, /diff, /plan, /compact"] 
  C17["<b>Config precedence</b><br/>1. CLI flags / --config<br/>2. profile values<br/>3. project .codex/config.toml root to cwd<br/>4. ~/.codex/config.toml<br/>5. /etc/codex/config.toml<br/>6. built-in defaults"] 
  C18["<b>AGENTS loading</b><br/>1. global override or global AGENTS<br/>2. project root to cwd, one file per dir<br/>3. root-to-leaf merge, closer guidance wins"] 
  C19["<b>MCP</b><br/>- configured in config.toml via [mcp_servers.&lt;id&gt;]<br/>- command or url, env/env_vars, timeouts<br/>- enabled_tools, disabled_tools, required<br/>- inspect active tools with /mcp"] 
  C20["<b>Subagents</b><br/>- spawn only when explicitly requested<br/>- parallel codebase exploration or multi-step work<br/>- extra tokens, but better isolation and fan-out"] 
  C21["<b>Hooks lifecycle</b><br/>- deterministic scripts during Codex lifecycle<br/>- SessionStart, PreToolUse, PermissionRequest<br/>- PostToolUse, UserPromptSubmit, Stop<br/>- current docs say keep codex_hooks explicit"] 

  C22["<b>System config</b><br/>- lowest normal config file layer above defaults<br/>- useful for machine-wide defaults"] 
  C23["<b>requirements.toml</b><br/>- admin-enforced constraints<br/>- approvals, sandbox, web search, MCP allowlists<br/>- managed hooks, rules, feature pins<br/>- not a normal project-team config"] 
  C24["<b>managed_config.toml</b><br/>- managed startup defaults<br/>- users can change values during a session<br/>- reapplied on next launch"] 

